OL,3,CSenior minister to warn Labour to
OL,4,Cresist leftward shift after by-
OL,5,Celection loss
OL,7,FAmong those calling for a change in
OL,8,Fdirection from Labour's leadership in
OL,9,Fthe wake of the defeat is former
OL,10,Fdeputy prime minister Angela Rayner,
OL,11,Fwho said the result should be a "wake-
OL,12,Fup call" for the party, and called for
OL,13,Fher colleagues to "rededicate"
OL,14,Fthemselves to "a Labour agenda that
OL,15,Fputs people first".
OL,17,FBackbench MP Clive Lewis (Norwich
OL,18,FSouth), meanwhile, told the Press
OL,19,FAssociation that Labour needed "a
OL,20,Fclean break" or would "lose the
OL,21,Fcountry for a generation".
